.TH CLA_get_value_optional 3
.SH NAME
CLA_get_value_optional \- Get the value associated with an optional command line argument
.SH LIBRARY
cla library (\fIlibcla\fR, \fI\-lcla\fR)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include \[dq]cla/cla.h\[dq]
.br
\fBconst char * CLA_get_value_optional (const struct cla * \fIself\fR\fB, const char * \fIname\fR\fB);
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B CLA_get_value_optional
gets the value associated with an optional command line argument \fIname\fR, using the
information from \fIself\fR.
.I self
can be constructed using
\fBCLA_create\fR.
.I name
can be either the argument's name or its shorthand alias, see \fBCLA_add_optional\fR(3).
.SH RETURN VALUE
A pointer to \fIname\fR's value. Any subsequent parsing is left to the user. 
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBCLA\fR(3), \fBCLA_create\fR(3), \fBCLA_add_optional\fR(3)
